node.text:
reminder: HEALTH is fricking WEALTH⚡️ 
-
-
-
my MANE goal is to keep it healthy for all my chicks
-
i like to do only TWO big colors a year and low maintenance in between
-
for the low maintenance appointment…
i usually do face frame only and leave the crown alone for the natural depth
-
BUT if you feel the crown has too much contrast with the natural add two baby low lights on each side of the part to soften the line

do you think i did baby lights or medium weaves on this chick?
-
-
-
if you guessed medium weaves you’re CORRECT
-
this chicks mane is way too thick to being doing baby lights… so to make more of an impact i did a medium textural weave and slice on my pickup to cover more ground

node.text:
want change? start with yourself⚡️
NEW CLIENT ADVICE:
-
-
-
1. always educate them on what colors work best with their complexion
2.  talk about the health of the hair and what steps to getting it healthy
-
sometimes you have to tell your clients NO to going lighter (which I honestly do a lot) 
-
in this chicks case her hair had been SO over processed from going dark to light and i wouldn’t be doing her any favors by adding more highlights for the health of the hair but especially for her complexion and washing her out… 
-
SO… we kept it simple with a 20 minute application of low lights to deepen her tone for her complexion to pop and a clear gloss over the existing light pieces to condition and add shine

node.text:
it’s all in the pull out⚡️ 
-
-
-
pulling out foils 101 →
pull 2 to 3 foils together by using my fingers to press the lightener through and letting it set for 5 to 10 minutes for an extra boost and even saturation 
-
for my highlights, i used my tangle comb to workout the tease and also softened my lines 
-
how do you pull out your foils? 
comment below xo
